3. COPYLEFT — DERIVATIVE WORKS MUST STAY OPEN SOURCE
================================================================================

  If you Convey a Derivative Work, you MUST:

    a) License the entire Derivative Work under this License (DTCL v1.0).

    b) Make the complete Source Code of the Derivative Work publicly
       available at no charge, in a manner that allows any recipient to
       download, use, modify, and redistribute it under this License.

    c) Keep intact all copyright notices and this License in all copies.

    d) Document substantial changes you made to the original software.

  You may NOT Convey a Derivative Work under a proprietary, closed-source,
  or more restrictive license. The community's right to access and build upon
  all improvements is non-negotiable.

================================================================================
4. SOURCE CODE
================================================================================

  When you Convey DevTent or a Derivative Work, you must provide the
  complete corresponding Source Code by one of the following methods:

    a) Include the Source Code alongside the binary or executable; or

    b) Offer the Source Code from a publicly accessible network server at no
       charge, with a clear written offer valid for at least three (3) years.

  The Source Code must be in the preferred form for modification and must
  include all build scripts and instructions needed to produce a working copy.

