6. PROHIBITION ON SALE — NO EXCEPTIONS
================================================================================

  YOU MAY NOT SELL DEVTENT OR ANY DERIVATIVE WORK. THIS PROHIBITION IS
  ABSOLUTE AND APPLIES TO ALL FORMS OF COMMERCIAL EXPLOITATION OF THE
  SOFTWARE ITSELF, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO:

    a) Selling copies of DevTent or Derivative Works, whether on physical
       media or as digital downloads.

    b) Charging any fee to download, install, access, or use DevTent or a
       Derivative Work.

    c) Offering DevTent or a Derivative Work as part of a paid product,
       bundle, subscription, or service where access to the software is a
       material component of what is being purchased.

    d) Operating a hosted or network-accessible version of DevTent or a
       Derivative Work (including "DevTent Pro", "DevTent Cloud", or similar)
       for which users must pay any fee.

    e) Using DevTent or a Derivative Work as a loss leader, upsell, or
       gateway to paid software access in any form.

    f) Accepting payment in exchange for a license key, activation code, or
       any mechanism that gates access to DevTent or a Derivative Work.

  CLARIFICATION: This section prohibits selling THE SOFTWARE. It does NOT
  prohibit you from using DevTent to develop and sell your own separate
  applications, websites, or services — so long as you are not selling
  DevTent itself or a Derivative Work of it.

  CLARIFICATION: Voluntary, unconditional donations to support development
  are permitted, provided donors receive no exclusive access, features, or
  copies that non-donors cannot obtain freely.

